<h2>Information Collected About You and Our Use of Such Information</h2>
<p>The following describes the types of personal and other information we may collect about you, and how we use and maintain that information:</p>

<h3>Contact Information</h3>
<p>In general, you may visit the Website without revealing any personal information other than technology-related information described in the section below.  However, to register with the Website, place an order, or participate in member interaction, you will be required to provide personal information such as, but not limited to, your name, mailing address, e-mail address, date of birth, gender, phone number, billing/credit card information and other information you may provide to us.  We also collect and store any personal information and other data you have provided to us via the Website, by email, or otherwise.</p>

<p>We use this information to respond to any inquiries you may submit to us, to track and monitor usage of the Website and to communicate with you about your account and your use of the Website.  In addition, we may use this information to send you periodic publications associated with Company and/or Company's products, unless you inform us that you opt out from receiving such communications via email. We also use this information to operate the Website; in particular, to facilitate postings on our discussion forums.  We may also use this information for targeted advertising and other marketing purposes. We may also use this information to measure the Website's effectiveness, tailor our products and services, better advertise to suit the personal interests of you and others, estimate our audience size, and any other use that Company believes may enhance your experience using the Website.</p>

<h3>Website Information</h3>
<p>The Website collects and stores information that is generated automatically as you navigate through the Website.  This aggregate information is collected site-wide, and includes anonymous website statistics. The Website also employs browser cookies to store users' preferences and record session information.  "Cookies" are bits of information that are stored by your browser on your hard drive.  This technology allows for the storage of user preferences, user ID and password, if applicable, and remembers you when you take action on the Website.  You can turn off the "cookie" function through most standard browsers; however, the majority of the features on the Website may not function properly, including but not limited to, the login and order functions, if the ability to accept cookies is disabled.</p>

<p>In addition, when you visit the Website our system automatically collects information such as your web request, Internet Protocol ("IP") address, numbers assigned to your computer by your Internet Service Provider (ISP), browser type, browser language, domain names, referring and exit pages and URLs, platform type, number of clicks, clear gifs, internet tags, landing pages, pages viewed and the order of these page views, the amount of time spent on particular pages, network traffic monitoring, active scripting, the date and time of your request and the unique identity of your browser.  This information is used to analyze trends, administer the Website, improve the design of the Website, track user movement, and otherwise enhance the services we provide.</p>

<h3>Other Information</h3>
